					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Steve Edwards</h4>
												<p>Steve Edwards is the author of <i>Rare Good: Essays on Art, Autism, and Astonishment</i> (forthcoming, fall 2026) and the memoir <em>Breaking into the Backcountry, </em>the story of his seven months of solitude along the Rogue National Wild and Scenic River in Oregon. His writing has appeared in: <i>The Sun, The Yale Review, Orion</i>, and elsewhere. Find him online: <a href="http://steveedwardswriter.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://steveedwardswriter.com&source=gmail&ust=1764776186913000&usg=AOvVaw3tW8I-N2kB6Bo1ARl4Fw6Q" class="external">steveedwardswriter.com</a></p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
